Algorithm – Hotel Management System
Algorithm:
Start the program.
Drop existing tables (if they already exist).
Create the following tables:
Guests
Rooms
Bookings
Payments
Insert guest details into the Guests table.
Insert room details into the Rooms table.
Create booking records by assigning guests to rooms.
Store payment details for each booking.
Display all guest records.
Display all available rooms.
Display booking details using JOIN operations.
Update room status when a room is booked.
Calculate total hotel revenue from the Payments table.
Display booking history for a specific guest.
During checkout:
Delete payment record.
Delete booking record.
Update room status to Available.
Display the updated booking records.
End the program.




